The paper proposes a method for learning speech representations without supervision, which is a problem in machine learning. The paper also mentions the use of neural encoders and discriminators, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SD (Sound), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the discovery of general representations, which is a common goal in artificial intelligence (AI) research, making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the paper proposes a method for learning transferable features, which is a common goal in computer systems and networking (cs.SY), making it a less likely but still possible sub-category.
